{
  "id": "L19",
  "title": "A casa di un amico",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "Welcome! In this lesson, you'll learn how to be a guest at an Italian friend's home. We'll start with arriving and greetings."
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L19_E01",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Ciao",
        "meaning": "Hello / Hi / Bye"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L19_V01",
      "data": {
        "Una bottiglia di vino": "A bottle of wine"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L19_V02",
      "data": {
        "I fiori": "The flowers"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L19_E02",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Questo è per te",
        "meaning": "This is for you"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "pronunciation",
      "item_id": "L19_P01",
      "data": {
        "word": "bottiglia",
        "phonetic": "/botˈtiʎʎa/",
        "tip": "The 'gli' sound is similar to the 'lli' in the English word 'million'."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L19_V03",
      "data": {
        "La casa": "The house"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L19_E03",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Che bella casa!",
        "meaning": "What a nice house!"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "pronunciation",
      "item_id": "L19_P02",
      "data": {
        "word": "Che",
        "phonetic": "/ke/",
        "tip": "In Italian, 'che' is always a hard 'k' sound, never 'ch' like in 'chair'."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "interactive_scenario",
      "scenario_id": "L19_S01",
      "title": "Arriving at Giulia's home",
      "setting": "You've just arrived at your friend Giulia's home. The door opens.",
      "conversation_flow": [
        {
          "title": "Greet Giulia",
          "chatbot_message": "Ciao! Entra, entra!"
        },
        {
          "title": "Give your gift",
          "chatbot_message": "Che piacere vederti!",
          "user_options": [
            "Questo è per te. Una bottiglia di vino.",
            "Questo è per te. I fiori."
          ]
        },
        {
          "title": "Compliment her home",
          "chatbot_message": "Oh, grazie! Non dovevi. Prego, fai come se fossi a casa tua."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "Great! Now let's learn how to handle small talk and accept a drink."
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L19_E04",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Sì, grazie",
        "meaning": "Yes, please"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L19_V04",
      "data": {
        "Un po' d'acqua": "A bit of water"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L19_V05",
      "data": {
        "Un caffè": "A coffee"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L19_E05",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Io prendo...",
        "meaning": "I'll have... / I'll take..."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L19_E06",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Com'è andata la settimana?",
        "meaning": "How was the week?"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L19_V06",
      "data": {
        "La cucina": "The kitchen"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L19_E07",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Posso aiutare?",
        "meaning": "Can I help?"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "interactive_scenario",
      "scenario_id": "L19_S02",
      "title": "Having a drink",
      "setting": "You are now inside. Giulia offers you something to drink.",
      "conversation_flow": [
        {
          "title": "Accept a drink and state your preference",
          "chatbot_message": "Vuoi qualcosa da bere? Un caffè, un po' d'acqua?",
          "user_options": [
            "Sì, grazie. Prendo un po' d'acqua.",
            "Sì, grazie. Prendo un caffè."
          ]
        },
        {
          "title": "Ask about her week",
          "chatbot_message": "Certo! Ecco a te. Siediti."
        },
        {
          "title": "Offer to help in the kitchen",
          "chatbot_message": "È andata bene, molto lavoro. Ma ora un po' di relax!"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "Excellent! The evening is coming to an end. Let's learn how to say goodbye."
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L19_E08",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "È tardi",
        "meaning": "It's late"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L19_V07",
      "data": {
        "La serata": "The evening"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L19_E09",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Grazie per la bella serata",
        "meaning": "Thanks for the lovely evening"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L19_E10",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Adesso vado",
        "meaning": "I'm going now"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L19_E11",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "A presto",
        "meaning": "See you soon"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "interactive_scenario",
      "scenario_id": "L19_S03",
      "title": "Time to leave",
      "setting": "You've had a nice chat, but now it's time to go home.",
      "conversation_flow": [
        {
          "title": "State that it's getting late",
          "chatbot_message": "No, grazie, è tutto pronto. Rilassati!"
        },
        {
          "title": "Thank Giulia for the evening",
          "chatbot_message": "Sì, il tempo vola!"
        },
        {
          "title": "Say goodbye",
          "chatbot_message": "Grazie a te per la visita! Mi ha fatto molto piacere."
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}